  "prompt": "Who should file income tax return?",
  "response": "In India, the following categories of individuals and entities are required to file income tax returns:\n\n1. Individuals whose total income exceeds the basic exemption limit:\n- For individuals below 60 years: \u20b92.5 lakhs\n- For senior citizens (60-80 years): \u20b93 lakhs\n- For super senior citizens (above 80 years): \u20b95 lakhs\n\n2. Persons with:\n- Income from business or profession\n- Agricultural income over \u20b95,000\n- Foreign assets or income\n- Capital gains\n- Income from multiple sources\n\n3. Companies and firms, regardless of profit or loss\n\n4. Individuals who:\n- Have deposited more than \u20b91 crore in current accounts\n- Have spent more than \u20b92 lakhs on foreign travel\n- Want to claim tax refunds\n- Want to carry forward losses\n\n5. Individuals who:\n- Claim tax deductions under various sections\n- Have TDS deducted from their income\n\n6. Non-residents with taxable income in India\n\nEven if your income is below the basic exemption limit, filing returns can be beneficial for future financial transactions and documentation.",
